Observation model for continuous assays with no added noise

Source: R/observation_models.R
observation_model_continuous.Rd

This observation model observes the latent biomarker quantities given a continuous assay with no added noise. Therefore the observed biomarker quantity is simply given by the true latent biomarker quantity.

Usage

observation_model_continuous(biomarker_states, model_pars, ...)

Arguments

biomarker_states

tibble containing true biomarker quantities for all individuals across all time steps and biomarkers. Variables should include: 1) i: the individual ID; 2) t: the time period; 3) b: the biomarker ID; 4) value: the latent biomarker quantity for the given i, t and b

model_pars

a tibble containing information for all parameters needed to simulate the observation process. This should usually contain: 1) exposure_id: numeric exposure ID; 2) biomarker_id: numeric biomarker ID; 3) name: the character name of the parameter; 4) mean: numeric mean of this parameter distribution; 5) sd: the numeric standard deviation of the parameter distribution

...

Additional arguments

Value

biomarker_states is returned with a new column, observed, for observed biomarker quantities

See also

Other observation_model: observation_model_continuous_bounded_noise(), observation_model_continuous_bounded(), observation_model_continuous_noise(), observation_model_discrete_noise(), observation_model_discrete()

Examples

observation_model_continuous(example_biomarker_states, NULL)
